gep

Class GepResult<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gep.GepResult<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The return type of a node in the encoded expression tree (=the type of gene elements) and therefore the type used by individuals.

    public class GepResult<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents the result of a GEP run and includes meta information and information about the best individual.
    Author:
    Johannes Wortmann

      • isOptimalSolution

        public boolean isOptimalSolution(double epsilon)
        Returns true if an optimal solution was found. False otherwise. An optimal solution has been found if there is an individual that reached the target fitness.
        Parameters:
        epsilon - The error allowed when comparing the floating point fitness values
        Returns:
        True, if optimal solution was found. False, otherwise.
